&lt;div class="highlight-none notranslate"&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;With CircuitPython now supporting a camera, it would be nice to have a
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;camera shield to use with my robot &lt;a class="reference internal" href="../../../projects/project-180025/#project-180025"&gt;&lt;span class="std std-ref"&gt;Fluffbug&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; . The OV2640 camera module is pretty powerful (it can create JPEG data
to stream), and the S2 Mini has enough pins to drive it, so the only
inconvenience left are three voltages need for powering the camera.
The shield takes care of that.&lt;/p&gt;
